# Class Calendar Implementation - Outstanding Items

This document tracks the remaining outstanding items for the class calendar implementation.

## High Priority

### Class Conflict Detection (WEC-27) - âœ… COMPLETED
Implementation of a system to detect and warn about potential conflicts when scheduling classes.

## Medium Priority

### Bulk Class Operations (WEC-30)
Functionality for performing operations on multiple classes at once.

**Description:**
- Implement bulk edit, delete, and status change operations for selected classes
- Add checkboxes to class list view for selection
- Create bulk action dropdown menu
- Implement confirmation dialogs for destructive actions

**Affected Components:**
- class-capture.js
- ClassController.php
- class-capture-partials/class-management.php

### Multi-View Calendar Options (WEC-29)
Additional calendar view options beyond month/week views.

**Description:**
- Add day view, agenda view, and resource view options to the calendar interface
- Implement view persistence (remember user's last selected view)
- Add view-specific settings and configurations
- Ensure responsive behavior across all views

**Affected Components:**
- class-capture.js
- class-capture-partials/calendar-view.php

### Recurring Schedule Templates (WEC-26)
Ability to save and reuse common recurring schedule patterns.

**Description:**
- Create UI for saving current schedule pattern as a template
- Implement template management (save, edit, delete)
- Add template selection dropdown when creating new classes
- Apply template data to schedule form when selected

**Affected Components:**
- class-capture.js
- class-capture-partials/recurring-schedule.php

### Batch Learner Management (WEC-18)
Functionality to add multiple learners at once.

**Description:**
- Add 'Select All' option for learner selection
- Implement batch processing functionality for learner selection
- Create UI for filtering and searching learners
- Add bulk status change options for selected learners

**Affected Components:**
- class-capture.js
- class-capture-partials/class-learners.php

## Low Priority

### Drag-and-Drop Exception Date Management (WEC-25)
Click-to-add functionality for exception dates directly on the calendar.

**Description:**
- Implement click-to-add functionality for exception dates on the calendar view
- Add visual indicators for exception dates on the calendar
- Create drag-and-drop interface for moving exception dates
- Implement right-click context menu for exception date management

**Affected Components:**
- class-capture.js
- class-schedule-form.js

### Calendar Export Integration (WEC-28)
Export calendar data to external systems.

**Description:**
- Add export options for calendar data (iCal, CSV, etc.)
- Implement export filters (date range, class type, etc.)
- Create UI for configuring export options
- Add scheduled export functionality for automated exports

**Affected Components:**
- class-capture.js
- ClassController.php
- class-capture-partials/export-options.php
